479 Convent Avenue, a three-story frame residence at the S.E. corner of 151st Street. Also shown is 416 West 151st Street, a two-story frame house at the S.E. corner of Amsterdam Avenue.
1932.

J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.

(1)
479 Convent Ave., at the S.E. corner of West 151st Street. Also shown is West 151st Street, south side, east from and including Convent, to, but not including St. Nicholas Ave. The 2 buildings Nos. 479 Convent Ave., and 416 West 151st Street are frame structures.

September 1, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same; a rear view, from Convent Ave.

September 1, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
